 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🚢 Titanic Dataset — Complete Analysis\n",
    "### Data Cleaning → Preprocessing → Visualization → Logistic Regression\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "This notebook walks through the full data science pipeline on the Titanic dataset:\n",
    "1. **Data Cleaning** — handle missing values, duplicates\n",
    "2. **Preprocessing** — encode, scale, feature engineering\n",
    "3. **Visualization** — explore patterns with plots\n",
    "4. **Logistic Regression** — predict survival"
   ],
   "id": "title-cell"
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 📦 Step 1 — Import Libraries"],
   "id": "step1-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder, StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    accuracy_score, classification_report,\n",
    "    confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('✅ Libraries imported successfully')"
   ],
   "id": "step1-code"
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 📂 Step 2 — Load the Dataset"],
   "id": "step2-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# If running in Google Colab, upload titanic.csv first:\n",
    "# from google.colab import files\n",
    "# uploaded = files.upload()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Local path — adjust if needed\n",
    "file_path = 'titanic.csv'   # change to your actual path\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(file_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Shape:', df.shape)\n",
    "df.head()"
   ],
   "id": "step2-code"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["df.info()"],
   "id": "step2-info"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["df.describe()"],
   "id": "step2-describe"
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🧹 Step 3 — Data Cleaning\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.1 Check Missing Values"
   ],
   "id": "step3-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('Missing values per column:')\n",
    "print(df.isnull().sum())"
   ],
   "id": "step3-missing"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Visualise missing values ──────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "missing = df.isnull().sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "ax = missing.plot(kind='bar', color='skyblue', figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "plt.title('Missing Values per Column', fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Count of Missing Values')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Column')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add count labels above each bar\n",
    "for index, value in enumerate(missing):\n",
    "    plt.text(index, value + 5, str(value),\n",
    "             ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step3-missing-plot"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 3.2 Handle Missing Values"],
   "id": "step3-handle-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Cabin: 687 missing (~77%) — drop the column entirely\n",
    "df = df.drop(columns=['Cabin'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Age: 177 missing — fill with median (robust to outliers)\n",
    "df['Age'] = df['Age'].fillna(df['Age'].median())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Embarked: 2 missing — fill with mode (most frequent port)\n",
    "df['Embarked'] = df['Embarked'].fillna(df['Embarked'].mode()[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Missing values AFTER cleaning:')\n",
    "print(df.isnull().sum())"
   ],
   "id": "step3-handle-code"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 3.3 Check and Remove Duplicates"],
   "id": "step3-dup-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('Duplicate rows:', df.duplicated().sum())\n",
    "# No duplicates expected in Titanic, but we drop just in case\n",
    "df = df.drop_duplicates()\n",
    "print('Shape after removing duplicates:', df.shape)"
   ],
   "id": "step3-dup-code"
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📊 Step 4 — Exploratory Visualizations\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4.1 Survival Count"
   ],
   "id": "step4-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "survival_counts = df['Survived'].value_counts()\n",
    "print('Survival Counts:')\n",
    "print(survival_counts)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))\n",
    "sns.countplot(x='Survived', hue='Survived', data=df, palette='pastel', legend=False)\n",
    "plt.title('Survival Count  (0 = Died, 1 = Survived)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Survived')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Passenger Count')\n",
    "plt.xticks([0, 1], ['Died (0)', 'Survived (1)'])\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step4-survival"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 4.2 Survival by Gender"],
   "id": "step4-gender-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('Gender Counts:')\n",
    "print(df['Sex'].value_counts())\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nSurvival by Gender:')\n",
    "print(df.groupby(['Sex', 'Survived']).size())\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 4))\n",
    "sns.countplot(x='Sex', hue='Survived', data=df, palette='Set2')\n",
    "plt.title('Survival by Gender')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Gender')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Passenger Count')\n",
    "plt.legend(title='Survived', labels=['Died', 'Survived'])\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step4-gender"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 4.3 Passenger Class Distribution"],
   "id": "step4-pclass-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pclass_counts = df['Pclass'].value_counts().sort_index()\n",
    "print('Passenger Class Counts:')\n",
    "print(pclass_counts)\n",
    "\n",
    "labels = ['Class 1 (Upper)', 'Class 2 (Middle)', 'Class 3 (Lower)']\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 7))\n",
    "plt.pie(pclass_counts, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%',\n",
    "        startangle=140, colors=['seashell', 'lightgreen', 'lightblue'])\n",
    "plt.title('Passenger Class Distribution (Pclass)', fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.axis('equal')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step4-pclass"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 4.4 Age Distribution (KDE Plot)"],
   "id": "step4-age-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))\n",
    "sns.kdeplot(df['Age'], fill=True, color='skyblue')\n",
    "plt.title('Age Distribution (KDE Plot)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Age')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Density')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step4-age-kde"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 4.5 Age vs Survival (Stacked Histogram)"],
   "id": "step4-age-surv-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(9, 4))\n",
    "sns.histplot(data=df, x='Age', hue='Survived', multiple='stack',\n",
    "             bins=20, palette='Set1')\n",
    "plt.title('Age Distribution by Survival Status')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Age')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Count')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step4-age-surv"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 4.6 Survival by Age Group"],
   "id": "step4-agegroup-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df['AgeGroup'] = pd.cut(\n",
    "    df['Age'],\n",
    "    bins=[0, 12, 18, 40, 60, 100],\n",
    "    labels=['Child', 'Teen', 'Adult', 'Middle Age', 'Senior']\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(9, 4))\n",
    "sns.countplot(x='AgeGroup', hue='Survived', data=df, palette='muted')\n",
    "plt.title('Survival by Age Group')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Age Group')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Count')\n",
    "plt.legend(title='Survived', labels=['Died', 'Survived'])\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step4-agegroup"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 4.7 Survival by Passenger Class"],
   "id": "step4-pclass-surv-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 4))\n",
    "sns.countplot(x='Pclass', hue='Survived', data=df, palette='coolwarm')\n",
    "plt.title('Survival by Passenger Class')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Passenger Class')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Count')\n",
    "plt.legend(title='Survived', labels=['Died', 'Survived'])\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step4-pclass-surv"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 4.8 Fare Distribution by Survival"],
   "id": "step4-fare-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(9, 4))\n",
    "sns.boxplot(x='Survived', y='Fare', data=df, palette='pastel')\n",
    "plt.title('Fare Distribution by Survival')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Survived  (0 = Died, 1 = Survived)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Fare (£)')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step4-fare"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 4.9 Correlation Heatmap"],
   "id": "step4-corr-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Encode 'Sex' temporarily just for the heatmap\n",
    "df_corr = df.copy()\n",
    "df_corr['Sex_encoded'] = (df_corr['Sex'] == 'male').astype(int)\n",
    "numeric_cols = ['Survived', 'Pclass', 'Sex_encoded', 'Age', 'SibSp', 'Parch', 'Fare']\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(9, 6))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(df_corr[numeric_cols].corr(), annot=True, fmt='.2f',\n",
    "            cmap='coolwarm', linewidths=0.5)\n",
    "plt.title('Correlation Heatmap')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step4-corr"
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ⚙️ Step 5 — Preprocessing for Machine Learning\n",
    "\n",
    "### 5.1 Encode Categorical Variables"
   ],
   "id": "step5-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "le = LabelEncoder()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sex: male=1, female=0\n",
    "df['Sex'] = le.fit_transform(df['Sex'])          # female→0, male→1\n",
    "\n",
    "# Embarked: C→0, Q→1, S→2\n",
    "df['Embarked'] = le.fit_transform(df['Embarked'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Encoding complete. Sample:')\n",
    "df[['Sex', 'Embarked']].head()"
   ],
   "id": "step5-encode"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 5.2 Select Features and Target"],
   "id": "step5-features-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Drop columns not useful for the model\n",
    "df_model = df.drop(columns=['PassengerId', 'Name', 'Ticket', 'AgeGroup'])\n",
    "\n",
    "X = df_model.drop('Survived', axis=1)   # Features\n",
    "y = df_model['Survived']                 # Target\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Features (X):', list(X.columns))\n",
    "print('Target (y): Survived')\n",
    "print('X shape:', X.shape, '| y shape:', y.shape)"
   ],
   "id": "step5-features"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 5.3 Train-Test Split"],
   "id": "step5-split-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Training samples : {X_train.shape[0]}')\n",
    "print(f'Testing  samples : {X_test.shape[0]}')"
   ],
   "id": "step5-split"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 5.4 Feature Scaling"],
   "id": "step5-scale-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# StandardScaler standardizes features to mean=0, std=1\n",
    "# This helps Logistic Regression converge faster and work better\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test_scaled  = scaler.transform(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('✅ Scaling complete')"
   ],
   "id": "step5-scale"
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🤖 Step 6 — Logistic Regression Model\n",
    "\n",
    "### 6.1 What is Logistic Regression?\n",
    "\n",
    "Logistic Regression is a **supervised machine learning algorithm** used for **binary classification** problems.\n",
    "Even though the name contains "regression", it predicts **probabilities** (values between 0 and 1), not continuous numbers.\n",
    "\n",
    "Here it predicts **Survived = 0 (Died)** or **Survived = 1 (Survived)**.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 6.2 Train the Model"
   ],
   "id": "step6-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "log_reg = LogisticRegression(max_iter=500, random_state=42)\n",
    "log_reg.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('✅ Model trained successfully')"
   ],
   "id": "step6-train"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 6.3 Evaluate the Model"],
   "id": "step6-eval-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "y_pred = log_reg.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
    "\n",
    "acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
    "print(f'\\n🎯 Logistic Regression Accuracy: {acc:.4f}  ({acc*100:.2f}%)')\n",
    "print('\\nClassification Report:')\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=['Died (0)', 'Survived (1)']))"
   ],
   "id": "step6-eval"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 6.4 Confusion Matrix"],
   "id": "step6-cm-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)\n",
    "\n",
    "disp = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm,\n",
    "                               display_labels=['Died (0)', 'Survived (1)'])\n",
    "disp.plot(cmap='Blues')\n",
    "plt.title('Confusion Matrix — Logistic Regression')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "tn, fp, fn, tp = cm.ravel()\n",
    "print(f'\\nTrue  Negatives (correctly predicted Died)     : {tn}')\n",
    "print(f'False Positives (predicted Survived, actually Died) : {fp}')\n",
    "print(f'False Negatives (predicted Died, actually Survived) : {fn}')\n",
    "print(f'True  Positives (correctly predicted Survived) : {tp}')"
   ],
   "id": "step6-cm"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["### 6.5 Feature Importance (Logistic Regression Coefficients)"],
   "id": "step6-coef-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "coef_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Feature': X.columns,\n",
    "    'Coefficient': log_reg.coef_[0]\n",
    "}).sort_values('Coefficient', ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(coef_df.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(9, 5))\n",
    "colors = ['green' if c > 0 else 'red' for c in coef_df['Coefficient']]\n",
    "plt.barh(coef_df['Feature'], coef_df['Coefficient'], color=colors)\n",
    "plt.axvline(0, color='black', linewidth=0.8)\n",
    "plt.title('Feature Coefficients — Logistic Regression\\n(green = increases survival probability)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Coefficient Value')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "step6-coef"
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🔮 Step 7 — Predict on New / Unseen Passengers"
   ],
   "id": "step7-md"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Example passengers ───────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Columns: Pclass, Sex(0=F,1=M), Age, SibSp, Parch, Fare, Embarked(C=0,Q=1,S=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "new_passengers = pd.DataFrame([\n",
    "    # 1st-class female, 29 years — 'Rose' type\n",
    "    {'Pclass': 1, 'Sex': 0, 'Age': 29, 'SibSp': 1, 'Parch': 0, 'Fare': 71.28, 'Embarked': 0},\n",
    "    # 3rd-class male, 22 years — 'Jack' type\n",
    "    {'Pclass': 3, 'Sex': 1, 'Age': 22, 'SibSp': 0, 'Parch': 0, 'Fare':  7.25, 'Embarked': 2},\n",
    "    # 2nd-class child female, 10 years\n",
    "    {'Pclass': 2, 'Sex': 0, 'Age': 10, 'SibSp': 1, 'Parch': 2, 'Fare': 27.90, 'Embarked': 2},\n",
    "], columns=X.columns)\n",
    "\n",
    "new_scaled = scaler.transform(new_passengers)\n",
    "predictions = log_reg.predict(new_scaled)\n",
    "probabilities = log_reg.predict_proba(new_scaled)\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, (pred, prob) in enumerate(zip(predictions, probabilities)):\n",
    "    result = '✅ Survived' if pred == 1 else '❌ Did not survive'\n",
    "    print(f'Passenger {i+1}: {result}  |  '\n",
    "          f'Died prob={prob[0]:.2f}, Survived prob={prob[1]:.2f}')"
   ],
   "id": "step7-predict"
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📝 Step 8 — Summary & Conclusions\n",
    "\n",
    "| Step | What we did |\n",
    "|------|-------------|\n",
    "| Data Cleaning | Dropped `Cabin` (77% missing), filled `Age` with median, `Embarked` with mode |\n",
    "| Preprocessing | Label-encoded `Sex` & `Embarked`, scaled features with `StandardScaler` |\n",
    "| Visualization | Bar, pie, KDE, histogram, box, heatmap plots |\n",
    "| Logistic Regression | Trained model, evaluated accuracy, confusion matrix, coefficients |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key findings from the data:\n",
